      "author": "echore",
      "description": "Security hardening for the local `/clip` endpoint. No changes to the capture flow or the extension contract.\n\n- Payloads are validated and normalized before anything touches the vault; malformed bodies and unknown modes get a safe 400 response, and error responses no longer leak internal details.\n- Untrusted video ids are sanitized before becoming vault file names.\n- Note frontmatter values (title, channel, urls) are escaped, so quotes or newlines in a video title cannot corrupt a note's YAML.\n- Cover and thumbnail downloads are restricted to http(s) URLs with a 25 MB size cap.\n- An out of range port value in saved settings now falls back to the default 17183.\n- Video frames are saved with a `.jpg` extension matching their actual JPEG bytes; screenshots stay `.png`.\n- Docs: the network use disclosure now explains why the local endpoint is unauthenticated and what the worst case is.\n",
      "downloadCount": 0,
